[{"id":"VR625286","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. Figure 1 shows an asteroid directly above and far from a planet. Figure 2 shows that the asteroid is directly above but at a shorter distance from the planet. In both figures, the asteroid is moving downward.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR625286.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An asteroid is moving directly toward a planet, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. At a later time, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the asteroid is closer to the planet and still moving directly toward it. The change to the <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">planet’s</span> velocity is negligible. Which of the following correctly describe the change in the total mechanical energy of the asteroid-planet system, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta E sub total\"><math alttext=\"delta E sub total\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>tot</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the change in the kinetic energy of the asteroid, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta K\"><math alttext=\"delta K\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>K</mi></math></span></span>, between Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR625286_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta E sub total equals 0; delta K equals 0\"><math alttext=\"delta E sub total equals 0; delta K equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>tot</mtext></msub></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>=</mo></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>0</mn></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>;</mo></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mspace width=\"0.4em\"></mspace></mstyle><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta E sub total equals 0; delta K is greater than 0\"><math alttext=\"delta E sub total equals 0; delta K is greater than 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>tot</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>;</mo><mspace width=\"0.4em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>K</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta E sub total is less than 0; delta K equals 0\"><math alttext=\"delta E sub total is less than 0; delta K equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mtext>Δ</mtext><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>tot</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>;</mo><mspace width=\"0.4em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>K</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta E sub total is less than 0; delta K is greater than 0\"><mat